description:
God is everywhere. In the Bible, almonds symbolize God’s watchfulness and presence in our lives. He is mindful of everything that happens in our lives. God loves us in such a way that no matter where we are, He is with us.

Because God is everywhere, there is nothing hidden from Him. The Hebrew word for almond “shakeid” means “watchful” and is used to represent God’s watchfulness over His people. The almond tree is mentioned several times in the Bible and is one of Judaism's most important symbols:  the menorah.

It is a wonderful assurance that God is everywhere. There is nowhere we can go that He cannot go too. God is always ready to protect, guide, and care for us. He is a wonderful and loving Savior to those who accept His gift of salvation. #shorts

#GodisEverywhere #NothingIsHiddenFromHim #GodLovesUs
